                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 367.11/8.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">American Ambassador</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-11-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 6, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Would announcement of intended despatch of an American war vessel strengthen your
                    hands in facilitating adequate protection of American citizens and their
                    interests? It would probably take a month for any vessel of our Navy to reach
                    Turkish waters. If you deem it advisable to send one, what type of ship would
                    you suggest? What destination?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Adee.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
